<think>

</think>

A bounced email returns to the address specified in the "reverse path" (also known as the "envelope sender" or "MAIL FROM" address) during the email delivery process. This is typically the email address provided by the sender when the message was initially sent. If the bounce is related to a delivery failure, the email system attempts to return the message to this address so the sender is notified of the issue.
